You are here: Home / Faculty : Boryung JuFaculty : Boryung Ju





Boryung Ju

Associate Professor
Louisiana State University
School of Library and Information Science
274 Coates Hall
Baton Rouge, LA 70803

Phone: 225-578-1460
Fax : 225-578-4581

bju1@lsu.edu
 







PhD, Information Studies, Florida State University
MLIS, Library & Information Science, Indiana University-Bloomington
                                                              
Honors and Awards
ALISE Methodology Paper Award 2000
Eugene Garfield Doctoral Dissertation Fellowship Award 1999
 
Service for Profession
Co-Chair, American Society for Information Science & Technology (ASIS&T), Annual MeetingNov. 2013. Montreal, Canada.
Managing Editor, Journal of Information and Knowledge Management, 2011-
Editorial Board, International Journal of Information Science Theory & Practice, 2012 –
Editorial Board Member, Journal of the Korean Society for Library and Information Science, 2013-2014 (2-year term)
Board Member, Korean Biblia Society for Library and Information Science, 2010-2012 (2-year term)
NSF (National Science Foundation) Panel Reviewer – Division of Information & Intelligent Systems Division, 2004
 


Courses Taught
LIS 7004  Principles of Management for Librarians and Information Specialists
LIS 7409  Human Computer Interaction
LIS 7510  Website Design and Management
LIS 7800  Research Methods in Library & Information Science
 
Research Areas
HCI (Human Computer Interaction): Interface Design and Evaluation; User Modeling; Usability Analysis;
 Knowledge Sharing; Distributed Scientific Collaboration
 
Selected Publications
Albertson, D. & Ju, B. (2015). "User and topical factors in perceived self-efficacy of video digital libraries." ACM/IEEE JCDL 2015         (Joint Conference on Digital Libraries).
Albertson, D. & Ju, B. (2015).   "The criteria for video digital libraries: Categories of important features emerging from users’ responses "            Online Information Review, 39(2).
Ju, B. & Albertson, D. (2014).  "Users’ criteria of video digital libraries from a public affairs context"           ’14 Proceedings of the 5th Information Interaction in Context Symposium,  235-238. DOI: 10.1145/2637002.(IIiX) 2014
Jin, T. & Ju, B. (2014).  "Corporate information agency: Do competitive intelligence practitioners utilize it?”           Journal of the American Society for Information Science & Technology,  65(3), 589-608.
Jin, T. & Ju, B. (2014).  "Toward understanding the perceptions of information professionals about competitive intelligence work”            Journal of Information and Knowledge Management,   13(2),
Ju, B. & Jin, T. (2013). "Incorporating nonparametric statistics into Delphi studies in Library & Information Science"         Information Research,  18(3), paper 589. 
Ju, B. & O’Connor, D. (2013). "Beyond categories: A structural analysis of the social representations of information users’          collective perceptions on ‘relevance’ "Journal of Information Science Theory & &Practice,  1(2), 16-35.

 
